=head1 DESCRIPTION

Contains the metric and the summary statistic you want to calculate,
and the order in which to sort the results, for the utterances across
the user sessions with the bot.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Name => Str

The metric for which you want to get utterance summary statistics.

=over

=item *

C<Count> E<ndash> The number of utterances.

=item *

C<Missed> E<ndash> The number of utterances that Amazon Lex failed to
recognize.

=item *

C<Detected> E<ndash> The number of utterances that Amazon Lex managed
to detect.

=item *

C<UtteranceTimestamp> E<ndash> The date and time of the utterance.

=back



=head2 Order => Str

Specifies whether to sort the results in ascending or descending order.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Statistic => Str

The summary statistic to calculate.

=over

=item *

C<Sum> E<ndash> The total count for the category you provide in
C<name>.

=item *

C<Average> E<ndash> The total count divided by the number of utterances
in the category you provide in C<name>.

=item *

C<Max> E<ndash> The highest count in the category you provide in
C<name>.

=back




